parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or hesitate to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates to shift into gear
grinds when shifting
or fails to engage into gear. The transmission may also slip or hesitate when accelerating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ETB can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or hesitate to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or hesitates to accelerate
the "wrench" warning light illuminates
and the engine may vibrate or shake.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch pedal can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate to shift into gear, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
or the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the powertrain can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or hesitate to accelerate, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates to accelerate
loses power
or stalls
and the "wrench" warning light may illuminate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash, as well as unexpected deployments that can cause accidents or distractions while driving.
symptoms: Airbags deploy unexpectedly
airbag warning light illuminates
airbags fail to deploy in a crash
passenger airbag light turns on randomly
and airbag system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in repairing recalled airbags can leave vehicles in an unsafe condition, putting occupants at risk of injury or death in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Recalled airbags are not available for repair
dealerships do not have parts
and manufacturers fail to provide timely repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic throttle body can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or accelerate unexpectedly, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power
stalls
or accelerates unexpectedly
the check engine warning light illuminates
the wrench light appears on the dashboard
the vehicle goes into "limp home" mode
and the throttle response is lost.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without warning
the accelerator pedal sticks or becomes stuck
and the brakes may not respond properly.
